dump: L!This program cannot be run in DOS mode.

Use the Server Manager to define remote server connections. The server name acts as a local alias for a remote server. The TCP/IP Address corresponds to the TCP/IP address or DNS name of the remote server. The port is the Cach TCP/IP port number (default=1972) of the remote server. The Telnet port is the port number (default=23) of the remote server which accepts telnet connections.
